House Resolution 560
By: Representative Reese of the 140th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Dr. Michelle Au; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Dr. Michelle Au is an anesthesiologist at Emory-St. Joseph's Hospital, in
3 Atlanta, Georgia, and a member of the Georgia House of Representatives; and
4 WHEREAS, born and raised in New York City, she graduated magna cum laude from
5 Wellesley College in 1999, with a degree in Psychobiology, and received her medical degree
6 in 2003, from the Columbia University College of Physicians and Surgeons, in New York;
7 and
8 WHEREAS, in addition to her clinical work, Dr. Au is a public speaker and published writer
9 whose work has appeared in numerous prestigious publications; and
10 WHEREAS, Dr. Au was proud to be the first Asian woman elected to the Georgia State
11 Senate, where she served from 2021 through 2023; and
12 WHEREAS, in her first term in the Georgia General Assembly she was named 2022 State
13 Legislator of the Year by Everytown/Moms Demand Action for her work on advancing gun
