14 safety, and was named Legislator of the Year by the Georgia Chapter of the American
15 Academy of Pediatrics for her strong advocacy on behalf of Georgia's children; and
16 WHEREAS, Dr. Au's significant organizational and leadership talents, remarkable patience
17 and diplomacy, keen sense of vision, and sensitivity to the needs of the citizens of this state
18 have earned her the respect and admiration of her colleagues, associates, and constitutes; and
19 WHEREAS, Dr. Au, doing what she would do for any of her patients, answered a very late
20 call from Representative Teddy Reese regarding his mother and a very severe medical
21 situation; and
22 WHEREAS, thanks to the leadership, care, compassion, and direction of Dr. Au, Mrs. Carrie
23 Prosser, mother of Representative Teddy Reese, immediately received the appropriate
24 medical attention which the family is convinced saved the life of Mrs. Prosser; and
25 WHEREAS, she is a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation for
26 integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness; and
27 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
28 dedicated legislator and medical professional be appropriately recognized.
29 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
30 the members of this body recognize and commend Dr. Michelle Au for her efficient,
31 effective, unselfish, and dedicated public service to the State of Georgia and extend the most
32 sincere best wishes for continued health and happiness.
